For the sequence from entering Gymnasium to graduating from it (i.e. obtaining Abitur), we draw on data from the 1971 birth cohort in the German Life History Study (GLHS) (Hillmert and Mayer, 2004), which contains detailed retrospective life-course information. We limit our analysis to respondents who went through the West German educational system. To obtain net survival rates at Gymnasium, we calculate how many students with a given social background enter Gymnasium at the beginning (N2g
) and how many students with that social background graduate from it (N3g
).
7
 After listwise deletion, we end up with an analytical sample of 1209 cases.
